#Proposal for @DeBank:

Yesterday the final version of the DeBank helper extension was released. With this post I'd like to ask you to implement at least some of the features it has into DeBank natively:

1. Sorting the Hot stream by creation date (to stay on top of the most recent trending posts) or creating a new Trending stream as an alternative
2. Figure out the issue with Official accounts  https://debank.com/stream/497457
3. Hide reposts on the Following stream
4. Enable blacklist filtering

https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/debank-helper/dgddolafmoaeoiimojjfbelofoodnjcm

Hello my friends! Recently I've been working on a new tool called DeBank stats. It analyzes up to 100 user posts and creates a report that can be used for several purposes. My favorite is to find the right people to unfollow to free up the "following" limit. More information and sample reports can be found here:

https://vermi321.github.io/debank-stats/

Unlike my previous free tools, this one won't be free due to the time invested in its development and the time I'd still need to spend on generating reports, if there's demand of course üòÅ

I'd appreciate your feedback.

#Proposal for @DeBank:

It would be amazing to have a few additional tabs on the Stream page to keep track of user actions. What a person trusts and writes in comments is just as important as what they post or repost. This would allow us to get a more accurate picture of what a particular web3 user is like based not only on their words but also on their actions. Also, it would simplify our lives a lot to be able to see our most recent comments and jump back into the conversation in an easy way.
